{"lemma":"شَرُّ","slug":"شَرُّ","root":"ش.ر.ر","root_slug":"ش-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَرّ","root":"شرر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":30},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21995","n22003","n22004","n22268"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bad, to be evil, to act badly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to blame, to rebuke"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bad, to be evil, to act badly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bad, to be evil, to act badly"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَرَّ (šarra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"evil","examples":[{"text":"وَيَدْعُ ٱلْإِنْسَانُ بِٱلشَّرِّ دُعَاءَهُ بِٱلْخَيْرِ ۖ وَكَانَ الْإِنْسَانُ عَجُولًا","english":"And man prays for evil as he prays for good. For man is ever hasty."},{"text":"فَمَنْ يَعْمَلْ مِثْقَالَ ذَرَّةٍ خَيْرًا يَرَهُ / وَمَنْ يَعْمَلْ مِثْقَالَ ذَرَّةٍ شَرًّا يَرَهُ","english":"So whoever does an atom's weight of good will see it, / And whoever does an atom's weight of evil will see it."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"more evil, worse; most evil, worst"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَرَّ (šarra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ugaritic 𐎌𐎗𐎗 (šrr)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21995","headword_ar":"شَرَّ","root":"$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arirota","text_ar":"شَرِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, MF,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ar~u","text_ar":"يَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, Msb, MF;) and sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arurota","text_ar":"شَرُرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S accord. to some copies, L, Msb, K, MF,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ur~u","text_ar":"يَشُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, Msb, K, * MF;) and sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ararota","text_ar":"شَرَرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S accord. to some copies, M, K, MF,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ir~u","text_ar":"يَشِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, MF;) of which three vars. the first is the best known; and the last is strange, and disallowed by most authorities; (MF;) inf. n. [of the first or third]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ararN","text_ar":"شَرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and [of the second or third]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araArapN","text_ar":"شَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ir~apN","text_ar":"شِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is an inf. n. [syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, evil, a wrongdoer, unjust, bad, corrupt, wicked, mischievous, vitious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depraved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L, Msb, K, * &c.) The manner in which the K mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~a","text_ar":"شَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the two aors."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ur~u","text_ar":"يَشُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ir~u","text_ar":"يَشِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[only, omitting the most common aor., i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ar~u","text_ar":"يَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] obviously demands consideration. (MF.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arirota yaA rajulu","text_ar":"شَرِرْتَ يَا رَجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast been evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wrongdoer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O man"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arurota","text_ar":"شَرُرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ararota","text_ar":"شَرَرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S accord. to different copies, and K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~a","text_ar":"شَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ar~u","text_ar":"يَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He increased in evil, wrongdoing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (L.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~amaA takobaru ta$ar~u","text_ar":"كُلَّمَا تَكْبَرُ تَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In proportion as thou growest old, thou increasest in evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (AZ, L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $ar~ahu","text_ar":"مَا شَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, last sentence.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~ahu","text_ar":"شَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ur~u","text_ar":"يَشُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~N","text_ar":"شُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) with damm, (K, [which is said in the TA to indicate that the aor., not the inf. n., is with damm, but this is inconsistent with the common practice of the author of the K, and is evidently wrong,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He blamed him; found fault with him; attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him, charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, a vice, fault, defect, blemish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"something amiss."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, * TA. [See also 4.]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA qulotu *aAka li$ur~ika waA_in~amaA qulotupu ligayori $ur~ika","text_ar":"مَا قُلْتُ ذَاكَ لِشُرِّكَ وَاـِنَّمَا قُلْتُةُ لِغَيْرِ شُرِّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I said not that to find fault with thee, but I only said it for a different purpose than that of finding fault with thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or this has a different meaning, which see below, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~N","text_ar":"شُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado qabilotu EaTiy~ataka vum~a radadotuhaA Ealayoka mino gayori $ur~ika walaA","text_ar":"قَدْ قَبِلْتُ عَطِيَّتَكَ ثُمَّ رَدَدْتُهَا عَلَيْكَ مِنْ غَيْرِ شُرِّكَ وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dur~ika","text_ar":"ضُرِّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have accepted thy gift; then I have given it back to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without rejecting it to thee or blaming thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and without injuring thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, TA.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~ahu","text_ar":"شَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~ahu fiY Al$~amosi","text_ar":"شَرَّهُ فِى الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) [aor. and inf. n. as in the next sentence;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~rhu","text_ar":"شرّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oriyrN","text_ar":"تَشْرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$r~hu","text_ar":"اشرّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aro$arahu","text_ar":"شَرْشَرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spread it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a garment, or piece of cloth, S, or some other thing, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA:) this is the primary signification. (TA.) And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~ahu","text_ar":"شَرَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ur~u","text_ar":"يَشُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$r~hu","text_ar":"اشرّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$oraArN","text_ar":"اـِشْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~rhu","text_ar":"شرّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n. as above; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~aAhu","text_ar":"شَرَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAhu","text_ar":"شَرَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"without tesh-deed?]; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. [the preparation of curd called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoT","text_ar":"اَقْط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and flesh-meat, S, K, and the like, and salt, S, and a garment, or piece of cloth, and the like, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSafap","text_ar":"خَصَفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) i. e. a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to dry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$r~hu","text_ar":"شرّهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sprinkled it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, salt. (R, MF.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K","S","Msb","MF","O","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n22003","headword_ar":"شَرٌّ","root":"$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~N","text_ar":"شُرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, K,) the former of which is the more chaste, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ir~apN","text_ar":"شِرَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 629)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moral"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"physical;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (L, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrongdoing, injustice, badness, corruptness, wickedness, mischievousness, vitiousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depravity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil fortune, misfortune, woe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwrN","text_ar":"شُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) It is said in a trad., in a form of prayer, (TA,) used by the Prophet, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlxayoru kul~uhu biyadayoka waAl$~ar~u layosa A_ilayoka","text_ar":"وَالخَيْرُ كُلُّهُ بِيَدَيْكَ وَالشَّرُّ لَيْسَ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, * TA,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And all good is in thy hands, and evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrongdoing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injustice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corruptness, is not imputable to Thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil is not a means of advancement in thy favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of obtaining thine approval:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil speech does not ascend to Thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Poverty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  It is also an epithet, applied to a man, (Yoo, S,) and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyrN","text_ar":"شَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, A, Msb, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil, wrongdoing, unjust, bad, corrupt, wicked, mischievous, vitious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depraved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, * Akh, * S, * A, * Msb, K: *) [fem. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~apN","text_ar":"شَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is fem. of its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aY","text_ar":"شُرَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ar~u","text_ar":"اَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is used in the same sense, as will be shown in what follows:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yoo, S,) or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyrN","text_ar":"شَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, Msb, K,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraArN","text_ar":"اَشْرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yoo, Akh, S, Msb, K,) and of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraArN","text_ar":"شِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ham p. 514;) and you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN A^a$ir~aA='u","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ اَشِرَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyrN","text_ar":"شَرِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) A woman of the Arabs, (S, L,) who, accord. to some, was of the Benoo-'Ámir, (L,) is related to have said, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uEiy*uki biA@ll~`hi mino nafosK Har~aY waEayonK $ur~aY","text_ar":"اُعِيذُكِ بِا@للّٰهِ مِنْ نَفْسٍ حَرَّى وَعَيْنٍ شُرَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I charm thee by"},{"kind":"text","text":"invoking"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God, against"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1525},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thirsty soul, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a malignant, eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eye that looks at one with vehement hatred."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ar~u","text_ar":"الشَّرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The evil one"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Iblees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  [It is also used to denote the comparative and superlative degrees; like the contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa $ar~N minoka","text_ar":"هُوَ شَرٌّ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrongdoing"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA $ar~N mino *aAka","text_ar":"هٰذَا شَرٌّ مِنْ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN $ar~u Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ شَرُّ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the worst,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ar~u","text_ar":"اَشَرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) this latter being the original, (Mgh, Msb,) but rare, (K,) or bad, (S, K,) peculiar to the dial. of the Benoo-'Ámir, (Msb,) or unused. (Mgh.) The fem. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~apN","text_ar":"شَرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [like as the fem. of its contr.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorapN","text_ar":"خَيْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K,) and (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ar~u","text_ar":"اَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, * or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ar~u","text_ar":"اَشَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Kr) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aY","text_ar":"شُرَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Kr, K.) And [using the dim. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minoka","text_ar":"مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa $urayorN","text_ar":"هُوَ شُرَيْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a little worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ibn-Buzurj, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyr","text_ar":"خير"},{"kind":"text","text":". [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $ar~a","text_ar":"مَا شَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^a$ar~a","text_ar":"مَا اَشَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4."}],"source_refs":["Kr","K","TA","Msb","S","A","Yoo","Akh","L","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n22004","headword_ar":"شُرٌّ","root":"$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vice, fault, defect, blemish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"something amiss:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing disapproved, disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA radadotu h`*aA Ealayoka mino","text_ar":"مَا رَدَدْتُ هٰذَا عَلَيْكَ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~K bihi","text_ar":"شُرٍّ بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not give this back to thee on account of any fault"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but I preferred to give it to thee. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA qulotu *aAka li$ur~ika","text_ar":"مَا قُلْتُ ذَاكَ لِشُرِّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I said not that on account of a thing that thou disapprovest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (K, TA:) or this has a different meaning, expl. above in the first paragraph. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":["TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n22268","headword_ar":"شَرٍ","root":"$rY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the eruption termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arFY","text_ar":"شَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"described in the next preceding paragraph."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}